  "prompt": "Which friends do you think are the best - school friends or college friends?",
  "response": "Choosing between school friends and college friends often depends on personal experiences and individual circumstances. \n\n**School friends** may provide a sense of nostalgia and shared childhood experiences, having grown up together and experienced formative moments during early education. These friendships can be deeply rooted and may last a lifetime.\n\nOn the other hand, **college friends** are often formed during a time of significant personal growth and exploration. College friendships can be characterized by new experiences, diverse backgrounds, and a shared pursuit of academic and personal goals. They often involve navigating adult responsibilities together.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" friends can vary from person to person, depending on the depth of the connection, shared experiences, and mutual support during different life stages. Each type of friendship has its unique value and can be incredibly meaningful in different ways.",
